## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **State Management & Simulation Architecture**
> Instead of a complex, fragile multi-server setup (separate node express backend + React frontend + MongoDB container) which can be slow and error-prone to set up and run on Windows, we will build a **state-driven client-side simulation engine** in React. 
> 
> This engine will run in a unified React Context (`SecurityContext`). It will:
> - Maintain mock databases in React state (simulating the `users` and `security_logs` collections).
> - Simulate active HTTP request workers running in background timers, generating thousands of API calls per minute during attacks.
> - Stream telemetry into a simulated "Security Monitoring Layer" that executes the rules engine.
> - Update the Dashboard and Breach Timeline dynamically in real-time.
> - This delivers an identical visual result (showing thousands of requests/min, alerts, and automatic blocks) with a **100% reliable, single-command startup (`npm run dev`)** for your presentation.

