### Simulation State & Business Logic

#### [NEW] [types/security.ts](file:///c:/Users/ADISH/Documents/VS%20CODE/EY%20mini%20project/src/types/security.ts)
TypeScript interfaces for Users, SecurityLogs, AttackTypes, Incidents, and TimelineEvents.

#### [NEW] [context/SecurityContext.tsx](file:///c:/Users/ADISH/Documents/VS%20CODE/EY%20mini%20project/src/context/SecurityContext.tsx)
The central simulation engine. It manages:
- **Collections**: `users` (mock LinkedIn profiles) and `security_logs`.
- **System States**: Normal, Attacking, Blocked, Mitigated.
- **Traffic Telemetry**: Current requests/sec, total hits, normal traffic baseline, attack traffic rate.
- **Rule Engine**: Evaluates requests in real-time to detect threats (e.g. Data Scraping if request count > 1000/min, Brute Force if failed logins > 5/min, Suspicious APIs if payload contains SQL injections).
- **Incident Logger**: Records threats into the `security_logs` collection.
- **Timeline Generator**: Dispatches events to the Breach Timeline (e.g., Detection, AI analysis, Block command, Notification).

